INFO  2026-06-12 01:02:49,805 [shard 0:main] main - application.cc:736 - redpanda.partition_autobalancing_mode:continuous	- Mode of partition balancing for a cluster. * `node_add`: partition balancing happens when a node is added. * `continuous`: partition balancing happens automatically to maintain optimal performance and availability, based on continuous monitoring for node changes (same as `node_add`) and also high disk usage. This option requires an Enterprise license, and it is customized by `partition_autobalancing_node_availability_timeout_sec` and `partition_autobalancing_max_disk_usage_percent` properties. * `off`: partition balancing is disabled. This option is not recommended for production clusters.
